military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Died one day before twenty-first birthday","body":"Theodocia Pierpoint Walter Hayden was born August 20, 1817 and died August 19, 1838 — one day before her twenty-first birthday, in New Haven Connecticut. She had married Nathaniel Hayden about thirteen months earlier on July 6, 1837. The compressed marriage-motherhood-death cycle across thirteen months captured the period's vulnerability of young women in the postpartum period."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Named for great-grandmother Theodosia Pierpont","body":"Theodocia Pierpoint Walter Hayden was named for her paternal great-grandmother Theodosia Pierpont Walter — preserving the great-grandmother's name across three generations of women. The Pierpont-Walter-Hayden name chain carried family memory of the eighteenth-century North Haven Pierpont line into a nineteenth-century Hartford-County Hayden household."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"One son who would die at twelve","body":"Theodocia's only documented child William Walter Hayden was born August 7, 1838 — twelve days before her death. The son would live only twelve years before drowning in the Connecticut River in 1850. The Walter-Hayden line through Theodocia thus produced no surviving direct descendants past 1850."}],"slug":"theodocia-hayden-1817"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}